      • createStandardMarker

        public abstract MapStandardMarker createStandardMarker(GeoCoordinate coordinate,
                                     int size,
                                     java.lang.String text,
                                     int shape)
        This method creates a standard marker.

        Not all shape types are supported in all devices. If the certain type is not supported, platforms default marker shape is used. Actual shape created can be queried after instantiation using MapStandardMarker.getShapeType().

        Parameters:
        coordinate - An object containing the coordinates of the marker
        size - size in pixels
        text - the label's text or null if text is not needed
        shape - shape of the marker or null to use platform's default marker
        Returns:
        The MapStandardMarker object

      • createMapContainer

        public abstract MapContainer createMapContainer()
        This method creates a MapContainer that can be optimized. If the container is optimized, some MapObjects could not be shown in case their centre points are close to each other at the given zoom level. Typical use case is route waypoints, whose drawing depends on zoom level.
        Returns:
        The MapContainer object

      • createMapFactory

        public static MapFactory createMapFactory(int tileResolution,
                          int width,
                          int height)
        This method creates a MapFactory with given resolution, width and height.
        Parameters:
        tileResolution - the tile resolution, either one of MapDisplay.MAP_RESOLUTION_AUTO, MapDisplay.MAP_RESOLUTION_128_x_128 or MapDisplay.MAP_RESOLUTION_256_x_256
        width - the width
        height - the height
        Returns:
        The MapFactory
